result.execSummary:
The defendant Richard Leon Beliveau was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse, Penalties for Misdemeanors-Class "B"], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

CO: RMW, REP: Drost, CLERK: Liddle. ADA:  Alexis S. Mckinley   DF ATTY:  Dan Firkus   DF:  Richard Leon Beliveau appeared. Case called at 8:42 a.m. Court notes 16CF206 was set for a jury trial. Was advised there is a resolution. Atty Firkus recites agreement and recommendations.   Court reads charge and maximum penalty. DE pleads GUILTY to Ct 1 Operating with PAC 5th in 16CF206 and GUILTY to Ct. 1 Disorderly Conduct in 16CM66. DE sworn. Crt reviews plea questionnaire and informs DE of rights. Crt finds DE freely, voluntarily and knowingly waives rights and makes plea. Attorney's stipulate to the facts. Crt accepts plea, finds factual basis and finds DE guilty of Ct 1 Operating with a PAC 5th in 16CF206 and Ct. 1 Disorderly Conduct in 16CM66. On motion of the State without objection, Crt dismisses Ct's 2 & 3 in 16CF206 and 16CM255. Sentencing arguments. 20 days to file appeal. hml

Crt orders:

In 16CF206:

- S/W 3 years probation

-  6 month jail sentence. Huber granted. Eligible for good time. 0 days jail credit at this time. Bond revoked and DE is to be remanded into custody.

-  Complete all other programming as deemed appropriate by the COMPAS assessment and the Department of Corrections

- AODA and follow through with any recommendations

- $52.00 Blood Draw Fee

- 24 month drivers license revocation. Credit for administrative services

- 24 month IID

-   Absolute sobriety:  Zero alcohol, zero controlled substances, zero prescribed medications (except as taken and prescribed for you by a physician) in your system, on your person, or in your possession at all times. This prohibition includes drug paraphernalia.

- DNA Sample

- Fine in the amount of $1,769.00

In file 16CM66:

- 3 months jail sentence to run consecutive to 16CF206. Huber granted.

- Court costs in the amount of $243.00

- DNA Sample and Surcharge in the amount of $200.00

-It is hereby ordered, as a condition of the defendant's bond/bail in the above-captioned case, that he/she have absolutely NO ABUSIVE CONTACT whatsoever with the complaining witness, or with any of the following named persons and/or locations,  Bailey W.  The term "abusive contact" is hereby defined as a verbal assault or an intentional infliction of or threat to inflict physical pain, physical injury or illness, an impairment of physical condition, and /or sexual contact or sexual intercourse without consent.  The aforementioned condition of bond/bail is set pursuant to Sec. 969.02(3)(d), Wis Stats.

Further, it is ordered that if the defendant fails to comply with the conditions of his/her bond/bail that he/she may be charged with the offense of bailjumping contrary to Sec. 946.49(1)(a), Wis Stats.
